@anchor{Function iota}
@deffn {Function} {iota} n @&key start step
@findex iota
Return a list of n numbers, starting from @code{start} (with numeric contagion
from @code{step} applied), each consequtive number being the sum of the previous one
and @code{step}. @code{start} defaults to @code{0} and @code{step} to @code{1}.

Examples:

@lisp
  (iota 4)                      => (0 1 2 3)
  (iota 3 :start 1 :step 1.0)   => (1.0 2.0 3.0)
  (iota 3 :start -1 :step -1/2) => (-1 -3/2 -2)
@end lisp
@end deffn
